        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 5:27PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cass City, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cass City, Elmer, Wilmot, Decker, Snover, and Deford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
